				<td colspan="2"><span>Kiting is the least of my concerns. My main complaint is that now melody usefulness is 25% of what it was when grouped.
<br />

<br />
If you are chant kiting to farm something off a mob, then either melody works for you... and some might argue that the new melody works better. 
<br />

<br />
If you are chant kiting for experience, you are missing out on experience by not using charm kiting instead. 
<br />

<br />
I have found myself dotting another mob without knowing, with the old melody, while charmed pet fighting the swarm (happened usually when gathering the swarm), only to find out on next pet that there is a mob at 50% chasing me now. Nothing that a tap on Fade wouldn&#180;t fix though, after sending new pet to swarm.
<br />

<br />
I will keep doing feedbacks every time I log about it, something like &quot;Plz, add another command for melody, call it /jam or alike, to allow for both versions of melody to be available so bards get to choose which they find more usefull&quot;
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Oh, and I already thanked those who did /bug and completely screwed melody for most of us in the &quot;Thank you noobs thread&quot;. </span></td>
